Flask API with SQLAlchemy and Elasticsearch Integration to run a basic app with API exposed to create , update and list user to the app and items/products .

Setup
To start the server, run the following command:

bash
Copy code
./setup.sh
Once the server is running, you can access the API at http://localhost:8085.

Default credentials for accessing the API:

Username: admin
Password: password
Endpoints
Health Check
Endpoint: /health
Method: GET
Description: Returns a success message to indicate the health of the API.
User Endpoints
Get All Users
Endpoint: /api/v1/user
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves information about all users.
Get Single User
Endpoint: /api/v1/user/<username>
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves information about a specific user.
Create User
Endpoint: /api/v1/user
Method: POST
Description: Creates a new user. Requires JSON payload with username and password.
Item Endpoints
List Items
Endpoint: /api/v1/item
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves all items from the Elasticsearch index. Default list of products is empty (NULL).
Index Document
Endpoint: /api/v1/item
Method: POST
Description: Indexes a new document in Elasticsearch. Requires a JSON payload.


Contributing
Contributions are welcome! If you have any suggestions, improvements, or encounter any issues, please feel free to open an issue or submit a pull request.

